
  <sn><md>### Compound Profit {.text-center}

In the case of compound profit, the profit earned on any principal is added to the original principal at the end of each year, and this `total sum becomes the new principal for the following year`.

The main difference between simple and compound profit is 
- Principal in simple profit is ++fixed++ which is the initial value
- Whreares in compound profit the pricipal is ++dynamic++ ;it increases with new profit in each interval

**Key Terms:**
- **Compound Principal** – The `increased principal` at the end of each year (original principal + accumulated profit).
- **Compound Profit** – The profit calculated on the compound principal.<br>
Profit intervals may vary. Instead of yearly, profit may be given every **three months**, **six months**, or even for shorter periods.

::: .px-3 .py-0 .m-3 .border

#### Formula

**Compound Principal** = Previous Year Principal + end Profit<br>
**Compound Profit** = end Compound Principal - Initial Principal

:::
